iscellaneous interests - becomes our enemy. Christians showed it when they talked of keeping one''s self "unspotted from the world;" but lovers talk of it just as much when they talk of the "world well lost." Astronomically speaking, I understand that England is situated on the world; similarly, I suppose that the Church was a part of the world, and even the lovers inhabitants of that orb. But they all felt a certain truth - the truth that the moment you love anything the world becomes your foe.', 263, 0), (126418, 'Trust God, He will care for your every need.', 2878, 0), (126419, 'How beautiful on the mountains are the feet of those who bring good news, who proclaim peace, who bring good tidings, who proclaim salvation, who say to Zion, "Your God reigns!"Isaiah 52:7', 24296, 0), (126420, 'A Christian who rebels against God’s Word is not a Christian at all', 24297, 0), (126421, 'The pleasure of reading is the greatest solitude.', 2878, 0), (126422, 'The greatest solitude', 24298, 0), (126423, 'Christ alone makes possible everything you are as a Christian.', 4239, 0), (126424, 'I''m not saying that suffering is our fault. I believe we suffer because sin has taken hold of the world. And with sin comes selfishness and heartlessness and wickedness. But I also think there will be a day of reckoning, Nick, when God lays out all we''ve done and judges our actions. That''s not as popular to talk about anymore, I suppose. We all like to hear about a God who loves and forgives rewards. But He isn''t holy and just if He doesn''t deal with all those wrongs. I would never want to stand before God without having done everything in my power to extend His mercy to the people around me whenever I could.', 15282, 0), (126425, 'My faith survived because I realized God didn''t want this for us, He never had. I''m passionately looking forward to a new Heaven and Earth where only good exists once more.', 518, 0), (126426, 'The unconditional love that God gives us when we are in relationship with him frees us and sustains us; we no longer feel the need to prove ourselves according to worldly standards, we are fine just the way we are.', 24299, 0), (126427, 'God is good, and I love Him. Right now, God is permitting a very hard thing. Why, I don''t know, but I still trust Him.', 518, 0), (126428, 'I can tell the difference between the acts of a man and the acts of God. That''s why I still believe. I could always tell the difference.', 518, 0), (126429, 'Far be it from me to slow down two badass supermodels on a mission, but we have a problem," a male voice said wryly.I could see Christian out of the corner of my eye as we turned, his stance and movements almost synchronized to my own. We shared a look, our expressions almost identically similar, with arched brows and half-smiles."What''s the problem?" I called out, scanning the faces to see who had spoken."You''re a badass supermodel," Christian muttered under his breath at the same time, taking the mature approach, as usual.', 13096, 0), (126430, 'Each Christian comes from a different background, upbringing, lineage, and environment. But in Christ we are unified.', 4404, 0), (126431, 'If you think you''ve seen it all, put on your sunglasses, because you''re about to be surprised.', 7358, 0), (126432, 'As a Christian, you are not here to change the world; you are here to save the world. Jesus came to save the world.', 21584, 0), (126433, 'I write not for the sake of glory. Not for the sake of fame. Not of the sake of success. But for the sake of my soul.', 24300, 0), (126434, 'As you abide in Christ, you will have strength for today’s trials as well as for all tomorrow’s challenges.', 4404, 0), (126435, 'YOU might be limited by a life situation, but GOD is never hampered. Praise Him!', 4404, 0), (126436, 'The central truth that serves as the platform for Christian marriage — and for all Christian relationships — is that in Christ we are at every moment eternally loved and genuinely significant.', 1086